Step 1: Define the MenuItem model in home/models.py
Make sure you already have MenuCategory created (as in your previous step).
Now, add the MenuItem model below it:

from django.db import models

class MenuCategory(models.Model):
    name = models.CharField(max_length=100, unique=True)

    class Meta:
        verbose_name_plural = "Menu Categories"

    def __str__(self):
        return self.name

class MenuItem(models.Model):
    name = models.CharField(max_length=200)
    description = models.TextField(blank=True)
    price = models.DecimalField(max_digits=8, decimal_places=2)
    image = models.ImageField(upload_to='menu_images/', blank=True, null=True)
    category = models.ForeignKey(MenuCategory, on_delete=models.CASCADE, related_name='menu_items')

    is_available = models.BooleanField(default=True)  # Optional but useful

    created_at = models.DateTimeField(auto_now_add=True)
    updated_at = models.DateTimeField(auto_now=True)

    class Meta:
        ordering = ['name']
        verbose_name_plural = "Menu Items"

    def __str__(self):
        return f"{self.name} - ₹{self.price}"

Step 2: Create migrations
In your terminal, run:

python manage.py makemigrations home

 Step 3: Apply migrations

Then run:

python manage.py migrate

->(Optional) Install Pillow for ImageField
If you haven’t already installed Pillow (needed for image uploads):

pip install Pillow
